article.headline: Norfolk State 59, Howard 49
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Chakowby Hicks scored 17 points and had six steals as Norfolk State defeated Howard 59-49 in Mid-Eastern Atlantic Conference basketball Monday night. Tony Murphy came off the bench to add 16 for Norfolk State (13-12, 11-6), which scored 21 points off 16 Howard turnovers. Darryl Hudson was Howard's (5-21, 2-15) only scorer in double digits, with 19. Norfolk State went ahead with 13:56 to go in the first half and never looked back. The Spartans held Howard to 17 points at the break. Howard tried to charge back in the second half with runs of 7-0 and 8-2 to pull within four at 43-39 with 5:27 left to play. Howard then got within three at 49-46 with 2:22 left, but layups by Calvin Brown and Tony Murphy, combined with perfect free-throw shooting by Brown and Hicks in the last two minutes put it out of reach.
